         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [TB]: having gathered possessions; ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [SKT]: (all) accumulations have ruin as their end; ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [TB]: elevations (have going down as their end); [SKT]: conjunctions (have separation as their end); ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [TB]: receiving (the fruit of their merits and their bad deeds); ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [SKT]: (who have done meritorious [deeds]) [will go] to a good existence; [TB]: who have done (meritorious [deeds will go] to a good existence); ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [SKT]: will go to <hi>nirvāṇa</hi>, free from affliction. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch114"/></note><note type="remarks">On <ref target="http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=IOL Toch 828" type="external">IDP</ref>, recto and verso are reversed.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.21c <hi>bhogān vai samudānīya</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.22a <hi>sarve kṣayāntā nicayāḥ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.22b–c <hi>patanāntāḥ samucchrayāḥ | saṃyogā viprayogāntā</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.23d <hi>puṇyapāpaphalopagāḥ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.24b <hi>kṛtapuṇyās tu sadgatim</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">: cf. Ud1.24d <hi>nirvāsyanti nirāsravāḥ</hi>.</note></p>
         </div>
